1. Title: Innovative and Novel Way of Issuing Community Tax Certificates and Other Relevant Permits and Clearances as Digital Certificates
2. Abstract: This patent application describes an innovative and novel way of issuing community tax certificates and other relevant permits and clearances as digital certificates, which is non-obvious, efficient, and transparent. The proposed system makes use of verifiable credentials, digital wallet on a blockchain as a payment provision, and machine learning to automate and improve the process of issuing, managing, and renewing community tax certificates and other relevant permits and clearances.

3.1. Claim 1: A method for issuing community tax certificates and other relevant permits and clearances as digital certificates, the method comprising:

a. receiving an application for a community tax certificate or other relevant permit or clearance from a user;
b. verifying the identity of the user using verifiable credentials;
c. processing the application for the community tax certificate or other relevant permit or clearance and issuing the digital certificate or permit or clearance, if applicable, to the user;
d. maintaining a record of the community tax certificate or other relevant permit or clearance and associated data in a database;
e. receiving payment from the user for the community tax certificate or other relevant permit or clearance, if applicable; and
f. updating the database with the payment information.

3.2. Claim 2: An apparatus for issuing community tax certificates and other relevant permits and clearances as digital certificates, the apparatus comprising:

a. a memory;
b. a processor coupled to the memory, the processor being configured to:
i. receive an application for a community tax certificate or other relevant permit or clearance from a user;
ii. verify the identity of the user using verifiable credentials;
iii. process the application for the community tax certificate or other relevant permit or clearance and issue the digital certificate or permit or clearance, if applicable, to the user;
iv. maintain a record of the community tax certificate or other relevant permit or clearance and associated data in a database;
v. receive payment from the user for the community tax certificate or other relevant permit or clearance, if applicable; and
vi. update the database with the payment information.

3.3. Claim 3: A computer program product for issuing community tax certificates and other relevant permits and clearances as digital certificates, the computer program product comprising a computer-readable medium having computer-executable instructions embodied therein, the computer-executable instructions being executable by a computer to:

a. receive an application for a community tax certificate or other relevant permit or clearance from a user;
b. verify the identity of the user using verifiable credentials;
c. process the application for the community tax certificate or other relevant permit or clearance and issue the digital certificate or permit or clearance, if applicable, to the user;
d. maintain a record of the community tax certificate or other relevant permit or clearance and associated data in a database;
e. receive payment from the user for the community tax certificate or other relevant permit or clearance, if applicable; and
f. update the database with the payment information.
